Trim and halve the @Green Beans{150%g}.

Cut the @Baby Corn{60%g} into thirds.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} stems lengthways, then cut into thirds.

Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{2}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp} for the noodles.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot, stir-fry the broccoli for ~{1-2%minutes}. Add the baby corn, @Sliced Mushrooms{120%g} and half the spring onion, then stir-fry until just softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds} more.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the @Egg Noodle Nest{2} and green beans and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.  
> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together and to keep the beans vibrant.

Once the veg has softened, add the cooked noodles and beans to the #frying pan{}.

Stir in the @Black Bean Sauce{150%g}, @Soy Sauce{15%ml}, half the @Chilli Flakes{1}(use less if you don't like too much heat) and @Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.

Cook until everything is piping hot and the noodles are well coated, ~{2-3%minutes}, stirring occasionally.  
> TIP: Add a splash more water if it needs loosening a little.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @Salted Peanuts{25%g}.

When ready, share the veggie noodles between your #serving bowls{}, making sure to get all the black bean sauce from the pan.

Garnish with the peanuts and remaining spring onion.

Sprinkle over the remaining chilli flakes if you'd like some more heat. Enjoy!